<div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="http://www.breeasy.com">Breeasy.com</a> > <a href="http://www.breeasy.com/opportunities">Opportunities</a> > <a href="http://affiliate.breeasy.com">Breeasy Affiliate Programs</a> > Master Affiliate Earnings Calculator</div>

<div id="bd">
	<div class="yui-g">
		<h1>Breeasy Master Affiliate Earnings Calculator</h1>
		<%= form_tag calculate_commissions_path, :id => "master_calculator_form", :method => :post do %>
		<h2>Step 1.  Number of Direct Subscriptions</h2>
		<p>Enter the number of subscriptions, by paid plan type, that you expect to signup or sell directly to your customers as a Master Affiliate in your first year. The numbers shown are for demonstration purposes only.</p>
		<table>
			<thead><tr><th>Id</th><th>Paid Plan</th><th>Interval</th><th>Price</th><th>Commission Rate</th><th>Number of Subscriptions Sold</th></tr></thead>
			<tbody>
				<% Product.active.master.each do |p| %>
					<tr><td><%= p.id %></td><td><%= p.name %></td><td><%= product_interval(p.interval) %></td><td><%= number_to_currency(p.price) %></td><td><%= number_to_percentage(p.new * 100, :precision => 0) %></td><td><%= text_field_tag "direct_#{p.id}", 20 %></td></tr>
				<% end %>
			</tbody>
		</table>
			<h2>Step 2.  Number of Sub-Affiliates</h2>
			<p>Enter the total number of sub-affiliates and sales reps you expect to signup as a Master Affiliate.  Again, the numbers shown are for demonstration purposes.</p>
			<table>
				<tbody>
					<tr><td>Number of Sub-Affiliates</td><td><%= text_field_tag :number_of_subs, 50 %></td></tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			<h2>Step 3.  Average Number of Subscriptions per Sub-Affiliate</h2>
			<p>Enter the average number of subscriptions per sub-affiliate/sales rep for each paid plan.  The average number shown are just examples, please put in your own numbers.</p>
				
			<table>
				<thead><tr><th>Id</th><th>Paid Plan</th><th>Interval</th><th>Price</th><th>Commission Rate</th><th>Average Plans Sold per Sub-Affiliate</th></tr></thead>
				<tbody>
					<% Product.active.master.each do |p| %>
						<tr><td><%= p.id %></td><td><%= p.name %></td><td><%= product_interval(p.interval) %></td><td><%= number_to_currency(p.price) %></td><td><%= number_to_percentage(p.sub_commission * 100, :precision => 0) %></td><td><%= text_field_tag "sub_#{p.id}", 20 %></td></tr>
					<% end %>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			<h2>Step 4.  Review Potential Earnings</h2>
			<table>
				<thead><tr><th># of Direct</th><th>Direct Earnings</th><th># of Subs</th><th>Sub-Affiliate Earnings</th><th>Total</th></tr></thead>
				<tbody>

						<tr><td><%= @total_count %></td><td><%= number_to_currency(@total_direct) %></td><td><%= @sub_count %></td><td><%= number_to_currency(@total_sub) %></td><td><%= number_to_currency(@total) %></td></tr>

				</tbody>
			</table>
			<p><%= submit_tag "Calculate Earnings", :name => nil %></p>
			<% end %>
			<p>Assumptions - Calculates estimated earnings per year.  Monthly subscriptions are assumed to last a full year regardless of of start date.  All calculations are based on current plan prices, without any discounts or promotions.</p>		
			<p>Remember - These earnings are in the first year - You will continue to earn commissions on all renewals - up to  40% on paid renewals - and they're automatic!</p>
		
	</div>
</div>